<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Denver, CO 2/25/02 Genghis Con Day 1<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4548'>Jason "Qui" Keen</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4548&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> February 23, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Well, I am a ticking time bomb of Fury.<br>
- Mr. Furious, Mystery Men<br>
<br>
Me (Jason Keen) and my companion Sean Gilfoyle representing the Ft. Collins culture came to Genghis Con mainly to play some sanctioned LotR.  We were further inspired by the Multiplayer tournament that was taking place since we have so few of those in Colorado these days, and it is our specialty in this game.  However we drove down to Denver on Friday hoping to improve our Tournament ratings with much optimism.  After checking into the hotel, the Hyatt Regency Tech Center, and eating some seriously expensive hotel nachos, we picked up are decks and headed over to the LotR playing area.  To my surprise there were several players there ready to play some multiplayer Rings.  I had come under the impression that people loathed Multiplayer due to the copious amount of timed out games there have been.  On this occasion there was about 19 players which would mean four 4-player games, and one three player game.  I noticed quite a bit of the Collectormania LotR crew there, most notable were the Dieniega brothers who had a spoiler list of Moria, yummmmmmmmmm.  Another member of the Ft. Collins culture was there (well ok he&#8217;s really from Loveland) but Peter Cole an ex-Star Wars player was there in his first sanctioned tourney.  Several people were there that I have never seen, they were from a strange place called Colorado Springs, which is more than an hour away from Collins so we never go to those tournaments.  It seemed to me that a lot of there players had never done a multiplayer tournament before, so things were looking good.  I believe the prizes for this tournament was the standard packs, a cheesy golden Trophy, and a Legolas foil rare, which would be real cool to get, so maybe me or Sean can win this.  I slip on my cheesy Barnes & Noble One Ring and we get started at around 6:15pm.<br>
<br>
I (1531)* am playing: The Fellowship or Aragorn.  Small, small fellowship featuring Aragorn, with Moria swarm on shadow side.<br>
Sean (1533) is playing: Hobbit Stealth with Nazgul Death.  Pretty much sums it up.<br>
<br>
 *All ratings in this are based off of Multiplayer Ratings that were last updated on 12/23/01<br>
<br>
GAME 1<br>
John (1500) Ranger Fellowship and Moria Swarm.<br>
Jett (1500) Modified Gandalf Starter Deck (Just learned how to play before the Tournament)<br>
Jason S. (1500) Boromir and Merry Start with Nazgul beats.<br>
<br>
This was a interesting game because most of these guys had never player multiplayer before, so I had to give a free lesson.  I bid low, like zero and choose to go last.  John goes first (order of players is the order we played in).  We all got started pretty slowly, all of them getting down some of the other mechanics, I get a great shadow draw getting a Swarms and 2 Armories into play.  Since John was sitting to my left, that made him my &#8220;mark&#8221; or guy who I can always unload Moria cards onto.  For the most part nothing did anything to dramatic, keeping a slow pace, no one took a real beating until we got to Moria of course.  John was the first to move to site 4, I had drawn my cave troll early and he gave me too much for site 4.  I play the troll with some other scrubs to get him out, and John doesn&#8217;t have any armor so he takes a Beating with Boromir.  Next time it comes around to John I am able to do a pretty good swarm and kill off Arwen and Legolas, I believe, but it wasn&#8217;t good enough to stack on Frodo.  I would have to wait till he moved to site 6.  All the while the other Jason was moving along pretty good, taking ineffective beats from Jett and John, but he had not lost a fellow ship member and he had quite a few wounds.  John is the first to move to site six, and with the 2 armories and a descent stack, I am able to finish off the job I began at site 4.  With John out, Jett was my new &#8220;mark&#8221; although I lost some orcs due to killing someone off.  However I needed to keep both Jet and Jason from moving past site 7 just so they could get the times out victory.  Jett was easy to do because he had rather weak fellowship, me and Jason were able to kill a couple of his guys, so he was forced to stop.  Jason on the other hand was near exhausted on the Bridge, when he moved to six I had an ineffective minion play, but I exhausted his whole Fellowship (Frodo, Boromir, Sam, Merry, Aragorn) which would come into affect later.  I&#8217;d have to move my 2 man fellowship quickly to get to site six, and sty alive to get the timed win.  So I moved to the Bridge giving up Seven, and Jason played a weak Nazgul, which I was able to kill with archery and an uber Aragorn.  I moved to 6 giving up only 4 shadow removing the remainder of the last move with Fro-Dawg.  They couldn&#8217;t do anything to me, and I only had 2 wounds on Frodo from Stinging.  So I was able to get a Timed out victory due to have the lowest amount of wounds since me and Jason S. had 0 burdens, 0 dead, and both on site six.  <br>
<br>
Timed out win +6 Points<br>
6<br>
Highs: I killed somebody with the swarm, I thought my Moria is just a card drawing engine and a non-effective shadow deck.    <br>
Lows: None really.<br>
<br>
Sean didn&#8217;t do so well, I think he got 2nd or 3rd.  which is good cause I didn&#8217;t want to play him yet ; )<br>
<br>
GAME 2<br>
Charles (1500) Pipe Deck with Swarm Cheese<br>
Shawn (1500) Rangers and Nazgul maybe?<br>
William Dieniega (1517) His famous fellowship and the Eye of Sauron<br>
<br>
Well I bid zero and go last, and Charles goes first making him my &#8220;mark&#8221;.  William is highly rated player at this game, but he&#8217;s not so good at multi, so he thought he wasn&#8217;t going to do so good.  Anyways Charles moves along and adds some shadow I pass and William plays an Ambusher and a Watchful eye . . . uh oh.  If there is anything in the world my two man Fellowship CANNOT deal with is Eyes, Bowmen, and Hate, so I am ready to forfeit this game to folly.  Well Charles moves a second time after killing the ambusher and moves to Shawn&#8217;s site 3 which is the Ford ack!  I play an armory and William plays another Eye and Shawn plays a Nazgul.  Well I think I am already dead after Charles&#8217; first turn.  I think William plays some bowmen on Shawn&#8217;s turn..  On the next turns I get more stuff out for the swarm set up picking on Charles&#8217; weak fellowship to set up a stack.  So Charles stops at site 3.  Shawn stops at three, and William Stops at 2. It gets to me I move once I give up like 4 shadow, nothing happens I then get to move to three which turns out to be bad.  Shawn plays a pretty good Nazgul which I think I can shrug off, oh wait I&#8217;ve already taken 4 exertions from the gosh darnit Watching eye.  Sauron is upon me when Cantea comes down disarms Aragorn and drops the Blade tip and Black Breath on Gorn which exhausts him, and Frodo defends with Sting (Cantea was Exhausted) at site 3 I am pretty much dead.  My two members exhausted one will die at the beginning of next turn.  But then something happens that the ring does not expect ; )  Charles moves and I add more to the stack, and I dig for shadow cards since I know that I NEED to kill Shawn these gosh darnit Nazgul conditions to win the game.  So Charles lives through site 4, and it comes to Shawn.  Shawn moves to 4, with a fellowship of Boromir, Merry, Sam, and Frodo.  Charles playing Moria plays fool of a took and top decks 5 guys who all cost one.  So Charles plays 6 guys that are only like 5 power, but Shawn has no way to deal with the three that stack on Frodo, so Shawn dies, and I didn&#8217;t even have to kill him yay!  I lost the Breath and Tip, and I am still on Site 3 Wooo hooo, I live!  William moves to 3 with a Fellowship of 5, which is a solid Fellowship, and he stops.  I heal up, ahhhhhh, and then I move to site 4 adding only 3, nothing happens yay!  Then Charles gets ready to move to site 5.  Well what does he do here?  Well you know how pipe decks usually just unload the pot at one location to get the action going?  Well Charles had this idea that he can do that right before the bridge.  So he plays a tone of pipes, tons of old Toby, Elrond, Gandalf, etc.  I think he gave me and William like 23 shadow, I can just see it now.<br>
<br>
	Gandalf and the Fellowship are desperately running from the hordes of goblins that have awakened due to the fight in the Chamber of Marzabul.  They are surrounded by thousands of orcs, just then the Balrog makes some &#8220;oooo listen to me I&#8217;m a hellish Demon!&#8221; noises,  The hordes of goblins scurry off.  Gandalf obviously perplexed has forgotten what exactly may have been the demise of Moria. Just then he realizes, &#8220;Hey, lets get reallllllll high!!&#8221;  Pull out the pipe and old Toby and start to make little miniature smoking action figures of the fellowship with Gandalf&#8217;s uber smoking ability!  That would have been a good book.  But as it is, the little hash party sits there when the horde of ravenous Goblins realize that they want their fare share of the hash, but Gandalf refuses and bogards the stash and is killed along with the fellowship and Fro &#8211; Dawg.       <br>
<br>
Charles is a very dead fellowship player at the Bridge when me and William are cone with him.  So the turn comes to William, I have a huge stack on the swarms and two armories in play, William doesn&#8217;t really want to move, but the rule book says he has to.  So he moves to site 4, giving me like 6 shadow . . . all too easy.  The stack I had was crazy, like 3 Moria scouts, two runners, 2 wall crawlers, 3 scavengers and I think a Keyward and an axe came out.  It was silly.  So he dies to an uber swarm and I win a FULL GAME, first time ever for me!! <br>
<br>
Full Win +7<br>
13<br>
Highs: Wow I killed two players, and won a game that I was surely out of contention for from the get go . . . suffice to say the Cheesy Barnes & Noble ring has given me power according to my stature.<br>
Lows:  I feel kinda bad for taking out the hash party, would have been nice to sit down and puff some weed with them ; (<br>
<br>
That was a pretty quick game, so we look at more MoM spoilers (Final Cry!! OH MY GOD!!) and I steal the One Spoon from William for the duration of the break.  I feel happy cause I am in first place at the moment.<br>
<br>
GAME 3<br>
Charles (1500) Same Deck ; )<br>
Sean Gilfoyle (1533) Same Deck<br>
Jason S. (1500) Are we seeing a trend here?<br>
<br>
I bid zero and go fourth, Sean goes second which is of course key to Nazgul Decks in multiplayer.  Well, Charles moves first, does his thing.  He only moves once, I hope to move to 3 on my turn in hopes that the Ford will not come into play.  However, Sean moves to two and uses Thrors map to play the next site, which can be his.  He gets his ford out on his turn so I am gonna be in hell.  It gets to my turn, I get a Bow, Sting, and a Versatility to deal with the Ford, I move there and try to just outright kill both Nazgul Jason Saves one with All Blades Parish.  I have Frodo Stealth a combat and he takes a wound.  It could have been worse, is all I have to say about that.  Well Charles gets to move to three, which means the Ford&#8217;s waters will flow.  Sean plays some Morgul gates (he said he drew four in the opening draw!!!) played Nazgul Toldea and Nazgul Nelya.  He pretty much kills Charles&#8217; pitiful fellowship on site 3.  Sean&#8217;s hobbit move to three is of course uneventful, and same with Jason S.  I however get the double Nazgul action at the fords (Uber Gates Action from Sean) but I versatility and shoot them down with the bow I played.  The rest of this game goes the same, I don&#8217;t want to get into the details.  Oh well I finally get to kill Jason S. at site six with my super swarm, however I am never really able to put Sean away.  But we both keep stealth numbers pretty low so we are never really able to apply the beats to us, I however move ahead of Sean to eight, which makes Sean have to double move with his hobbits.  He however cannot not sine I played the infamous late game Cave Troll and swarm on site 7, and apparently Seam didn&#8217;t have the 4 Powers to kill my Troll ; )  So he stops at 7 which means I need to survive through site 9, I move there with a pretty fresh Aragorn, so he can at least Defender plus on and take two rounds of Nazgul, which would win me the game (Coat of Mail included)  which is how it goes down and I win the game with a full win.<br>
<br>
Full Win +7<br>
20<br>
Highs: Winning a full win . . . Again!  I thought Full games never happened in Multiplayer Tournaments??<br>
Lows: Playing Sean, I hate playing people from my culture.<br>
<br>
So I am still in first lace going into the last round but I still need to win more or less due to the wacky points system.  I can feel the Golden Trophy within grasp.<br>
<br>
GAME 4<br>
William Dieniega (1517) 19pts.<br>
Sean Gilfoyle (1533) 17pts<br>
Peter Cole (1500) 16pts.<br>
.<br>
<br>
Sweet, two people I play test with and William, and they all talking trash about killing me.  This is gonna suck.  Well I bid zero and go last of course.  We get the shenanigans going trying to avoid death from Sean&#8217;s Nazgul deck early on.  William didn&#8217;t get his Sauron action going right away which is good.  We all move and Sean doesn&#8217;t do too much.  Well I get an awesome draw Fellowship wise (Bow, Sword, Sting) and I move once and twice, hoping to avoid the fords.  Well I sting Pete before I move but he has a junky hand, which is bad, and I sting William he also has a junky hand, I remove ZERO shadow of the three I play.  So I move to weather hills adding 5 making the total eight.  Sean drops two gates plays two Nazgul, can&#8217;t remember which (Nelya and Toldea) and I have no good defense here.  Frodo takes Nelya twice, no bonuses but I take a Black Breath and a Blade Tip on Frodo (Exhausted Frodo) and I decide to stop.  It doesn&#8217;t go anywhere for me.  Next turn no Athelas, I move to three and stay alive, but I have a Frodo I cannot Sting with so if I play things I will be screwing my self.  Well realizing that I am not going to win I HAVE to kill somebody in order to get points to at least get second place.  So I decide to Pick on Pete&#8217;s fellowship because it weak, as opposed to Williams uber Archery.  When Pete move to 5 I bring out a money swarm and kill him (no details on the swarm, but it was gooood)  So that 3will get me at least 2-3 points.  I move to site 5 and I lose Aragorn, and I have to Powers twice to keep Frodo alive, I was able to Athelas the Black Breath before I died, but I still had 9 burdens.  William and Sean Target each other now, as I watch them play it out, I try to help out some before I die, but much of it is ineffective, and it didn&#8217;t matter for me.  It gets to my Turn and Frodo passes into the Shadowrealm on site six (Burden Death).  The rest is all a blur, the Ring from Barne&#8217;s & Noble had betrayed me, I think I kept doing bad impersonations of Sean Bean for the rest of the evening, as I say Sean lose to William from Williams super dupah Orcish Bowmen.  I get third, the Strength of Men had failed yet again.<br>
<br>
+3<br>
23pts.<br>
Highs: Hah, Exhausted Fro-dawg and Nine burdens in Galadriel&#8217;s Grove, nuff said&#8217;.<br>
Lows: I lost, all I needed to have happen was kill William and I win, but no, I sucked and I only got Second ARRRRRGGGG!!!!<br>
<br>
It goes down like this:<br>
1st place William: Trophy, Legolas, Gift Certificate<br>
2nd place ME: Two packs (one with a Witch King)<br>
3rd place Sean: Two Packs<br>
<br>
We&#8217;ll See how the Aragorn Deck hold up Tomorrow night in the 6 Round Swiss Tournament eh?<br>
